data.title: Dominique Hourani
data.text:
Dominique Hourani (Arabic: دومينيك حوراني; born 7 August 1985) is a Lebanese recording artist, actress, beauty queen, and former model.

Personal life

[edit]

In 2007, Hourani married an Iranian-austrian businessman named Alireza Nokiani.[1] Together they have a daughter, Delara Sue Almassi (born in 2008)..[2] She currently lives in Egypt and the UAE with husband .[3]

Modeling

[edit]

She won a competition with contestants from over 80 countries and was awarded the Miss Intercontinental 2003 title.[4]

Acting

[edit]

Hourani first appeared on the television series, Oyoun Kha'ena (The eyes of the deceiver),[5] alongside famous TV presenter, Tony Khalife. The series was broadcast in Lebanon and the Arab world on LBC.

In 2009, Hourani decided to go with her first movie El Beeh Romancy, along with Mohamed Adel Emam, Hasan Housni, Lebleba, Mena Arafa and Saad El Soghaier.[6]

Singing

[edit]

Hourani traveled to America and sang at an Arab American festival concert with more than 300,000 people attending.[7]
